%C A388262 Define S(k, p) to be the number of steps for the Sisyphus sequence to reach 1 when started at k, with p being the last prime used (p = 1 at the start). Thus, A388038(k) = S(k, 1). The record trajectories for 1008973 and its multiples (and for the numerous record ties between them; see linked a-file) are due to convergence to S(3, 269) = 3584971395. Looking for this drastically speeds calculations in A388262 and A388263. - _Michael S. Branicky_, Sep 21 2025
